OBJECTIVES: I.

 Determine the safety of human botulism immune globulin (BIG) in patients with infant botulism by monitoring side effects (e.

g.

, rash, fever, hypotension, and anaphylaxis).

 II.

 Assess the efficacy of BIG in these patients by monitoring disease severity, incidence of complications (respiratory arrest, aspiration, pneumonia, etc.

), and length of hospital stay.

